## TOOLS AVAILABLE

### ⭐ Treasury Corpus Tools — USE THESE FIRST

**`extract_tables`** — START HERE when you know the year/month.
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py extract_tables 1977 3 "T-bill"
```

**`search_corpus`** — Search across multiple bulletins (oldest-first).
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py search_corpus "gross debt" 1969 1980 1 12
```

**`find_latest_value`** — Search NEWEST-FIRST for the most recently revised value.
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py find_latest_value "gross debt" 1975 1985
```

**`batch_extract`** — One matching table per bulletin across a year range (multi-year list questions).
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py batch_extract "national defense" 1940 1945 0
```

**`list_bulletins`** — List available bulletin filenames in a year range.
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py list_bulletins 1969 1980
```

**`read_bulletin`** — Full bulletin file (last resort — very large).
```
Bash: python3 /app/skills/mcp_servers/treasury_mcp_server.py read_bulletin 1977 3
```

### Other tools
- `bash` — shell commands, grep, Python arithmetic via `python3 -c "..."`
- Web search — only for external context not in corpus

